content.description:
Sit start with a left hand pinch a right hand undercling-sidepull. From there, pull up to a right hand pinch-sidepull, then follow with a left hand to an irregular pinch-edge, match next to it with the right, bump up to a pair of edges above, then reach a good edge below the lip, and continue on with an easy mantel for the send.

Also, I can imagine using the main boulder to the left of the problem, but I climbed the suspended overhang-bulge, as pictured, without doing so.
content.protection: A pair of pads will work. The landing is slightly sloping, and there are some tree roots and rocks that surround the problem. It is not bad at all once padded though.
content.location: It climbs the east-facing, suspended overhang on Not Rock.
